Windows Defender Security Center is now on Windows 10 v1703 and later which acts a dashboard for security. 

It consists of 5 sections:

1. Virus and threat protection. It consists of controlled folde access to protect data and works with thrird anti-virus software.

2. Device performance and health. Monitors health like battery life, drivers,storage, and updates.

3. Firewall and network settings. Information on networks, sharing, and troubleshooting.

4. App and browser control. With settings you can adjust for online threats.

5. Family options. To keep track of health and safety of kids online activity & games, accces limits, and port configurations.

This is a win-win for everybody because it is a selling point for Microsoft and a easier interface for users to interact with.
